name: Quetzalcóatl
description:
Quetzalcóatl
Also known as "The Feathered Snake", Quetzalcoatl was one of the most important gods of the mesoamerican cultures. A mix between a snake and a bird. His name is the fusion of the nahuatl words "quetzal" 
which means emerald feather bird, and "coatl" 
which means snake.

Was considered as the god of the wind and rain, the creator of the world and the human being, the protector of the priests and merchants, the god of knowledge, science, agriculture, artisans, and arts.
